4. And finally, shoutout to our pal Melissa Sariffodeen, @melsariffodeen , of Canada Learning Code, who is on a mission to make coding education accessible for all Canadians. Her twitter feed is full of inspiring coding education stories we absolutely love. #ALD18 #STEMeducation

3. Dr. Merritt Moore @physicsonpointe - we found her in @rebelgirlsbook - she is a ballerina who has danced with FIVE ballet companies AND a quantum physics scientist with a PhD from Oxford. So, you see, choosing a career is overrated.
2. Samantha Yammine @SamanthaZY - hailing from our hometown Toronto, her IG account Science.Sam teaches us about microscopic biology and brain stuff we never learned in school.

1. Cpt Sunita Williams @Astro_Suni - woman astronaut - need we say more? Why we love her: she has this great video on YouTube giving us the tour of the ISS from her mission in 2012. She also holds record for total spacewalk time by a female astronaut. Wild.
